# ğŸ® Tic Tac Toe Game in C++

A simple command-line Tic Tac Toe game written in C++. This project demonstrates the use of basic programming concepts such as loops, conditionals, functions, arrays, and user input handling.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Description

This is a two-player console-based Tic Tac Toe game where players take turns marking X and O on a 3Ã—3 grid. The game checks for winning conditions and declares the winner or a draw accordingly.

This project is beginner-friendly and ideal for learning core C++ fundamentals and game logic implementation.

